Solid waste management is at the moment in the status of very fast development as it forms a base for the sustainable development of the society. Solid waste management and technologies in this field are nowadays covering strategies for recycling and recovery of several waste products, incineration processes of solid waste and also deposition and composting methods. To avoid hazards to the environment, solid waste handling must be implemented in sound way. Course will provide basic principles of new technologies and legislation in this field.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To introduce main principles of solid waste management and treatment processes.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Student 1) is familiar with the environmental strategy of the state and knows basic principles of solid waste management; 2) knows the basis for classification of different types of waste including hazardous waste; 3) is acquainted with legislation in the field of solid waste management and knows main principles of international cooperation in the field of hazardous waste management; 4) knows the hierarchy pyramid for waste treatment technologies and understands the sustainable ways of bringing it into practice; 5) knows substantial technologies for solid waste treatment and is able to compare the influence of different methods of treatment to the environment; 6). is familiar with priorities in the field of solid waste treatment and is has compiled the plan of solid waste management for local government using main principles from the state plan for that; 7) has participated at the field studies in different enterprises dealing with solid waste treatment. Has compiled an overview about the solid waste treatment technology in an enterprise and is able to explain and compare technological solutions for the enterprise.
